article.headline: SE Missouri 94, New Orleans 71
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. -- Corey Wilford scored 18 points, including five 3-pointers, and Southeast Missouri coasted to a 94-71 victory over New Orleans on Wednesday night. It was the second victory for Southeast Missouri (7-6) over New Orleans (3-7) this season. Southeast Missouri held a slim 42-39 lead at halftime, then went on a 16-9 run to open the second half. Nino Johnson scored 16 points and grabbed nine rebounds for Southeast Missouri. New Orleans had three men score in double figures. Corey Blake had 13 points, Cory Dixon had 12 and Eddie Denard had 11. Lucas Nutt had 10 assists for Southeast Missouri.
